The Boy Who Cried Wolf

Once there was a boy who looked after sheep.
He was very bored.

One day, he shouted, “Wolf! Wolf!”
The villagers came running to help him.

But there was no wolf. The boy laughed.

He did this again and again.
Each time, the villagers came, but there was no wolf.

One day, a real wolf came.
The boy shouted, “Wolf! Wolf!”

But this time, no one came to help him.
The wolf attacked the sheep.

The boy learned a lesson.

Moral:

Never tell lies.
